Global Cardiopulmonary Resuscitation (CPR) Machine Market Insights
Cardiopulmonary Resuscitation (CPR) Machine Market size was valued at USD 1.2 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 2.1 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.8% from 2024 to 2030.

Cardiopulmonary Resuscitation (CPR) Machine Market Overview
The global Cardiopulmonary Resuscitation (CPR) machine market size was valued at USD 3.4 billion in 2024 and is expected to expand at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 6.7% from 2024 to 2030. The market's growth is driven by the increasing incidence of cardiac arrests, advancements in CPR technology, and the growing adoption of automated external defibrillators (AEDs). As healthcare systems globally focus on improving patient outcomes, CPR machines have become critical devices in both hospital and pre-hospital settings. The integration of machine learning and AI in CPR devices is also enhancing their performance and reliability, creating new market opportunities. Moreover, the surge in the elderly population, coupled with rising health awareness, is further supporting the market's expansion.

